    "body": "@rachelhamlin could you clarify please this part: `- but has the same user pic`. You mean this contact has **default** userpic or the one which was **set by you**?\r\n\r\nFor this moment the logic of revealing contact names and userpics is next:\r\n1) You and me have a contact with the non-default username and userpic.\r\n2) You want to chat me and send a request following by text message. However until I \"share\" my details to you (via 'Add to contacts' button in 1-1 chat) you see me with the default username and userpic. But I want to know who is going to message me - so on my side your contact name and userpic are revealed (i.e. non-default)\r\n3) I add you to my contacts and you see my \"real\" name and avatar.\r\n\r\nSo it is expected that non-default contact name and userpic of other contacts are shown to me when other contacts are sending me a contact request.\r\nIt is not expected that one of two - contact name or userpic - is shown as non-default but another with the default value.",
